band's%20health%20scare%20helped%20put%20life%20and%20retirement%20into%20perspective%20for%20her.%3Cp%3EShubhangi%20Goel%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKim%20Hunter-Borst%20is%20retiring%20from%20her%20job%20this%20month%20after%20delaying%20it%20for%20several%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20she%20attached%20her%20identity%20to%20her%20career%2C%20but%20her%20husband%20helped%20her%20reevaluate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20retirement%20plans%20include%20financial%20independence%20events%20for%20women%20and%20more%20neighborhood%20events.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Kim%20Hunter-Borst%2C%2057%2C%20a%20healthcare%20professional%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20got%20married%20when%20we%20were%20a%20bit%20older.%20I%20was%2042%20and%20he%20was%2049%2C%20and%20he%20had%20two%20children%20already.%20I%20saw%20my%20role%20in%20our%20family%20as%20the%20person%20who%20brought%20in%20all%20the%20fun.%20We%20just%20lived%20life%20thinking%20there%20was%20always%20a%20paycheck%20coming%20around%20the%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20in%20healthcare%20and%20always%20thought%20my%20job%20was%20recession-proof.%20But%20when%20I%20had%20to%20lay%20off%20people%20in%202016%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20we%20had%20no%20financial%20cushion%20if%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20to%20lose%20our%20jobs.%20We%20were%20both%20earning%20well%2C%20but%20somehow%2C%20we%20were%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%2C%20something%20that%20feels%20so%20normal%20in%20American%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ef7917fe-e9f0-4e8f-ad60-5153be61ebe1%5C%22%3EI%20was%20embarrassed%20to%20say%20we%20messed%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20layoffs%2C%20I%20audited%20our%20finances%20and%20saw%20that%20we%20were%20%2469%2C000%20in%20debt.%20Our%20oldest%20kid%20was%20ready%20to%20go%20to%20college%2C%20and%20losing%20our%20jobs%20would%20mean%20tapping%20into%20our%20savings%20to%20pay%20for%20it.%20I%20had%20about%20%24219%2C000%20in%20savings%20because%20someone%20early%20in%20my%20career%20advised%20me%20to%20put%203%25%20in%20my%20401(k).%20My%20husband%2C%20who%20had%20been%20divorced%20and%20raising%20kids%20on%20his%20own%2C%20had%20%2417%2C000%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20savings.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20live%20with%20that%20anxiety%20and%20wanted%20to%20be%20debt-free%20and%20credit-card-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20in%20our%20forties%20and%20in%20good%20careers.%20It%20felt%20embarrassing%20to%20admit%20to%20others%20that%20we%20had%20messed%20up%20and%20were%20in%20debt.%20I'm%20not%20ashamed%20of%20it%20now%2C%20but%20we%20used%20to%20make%20excuses%20about%20missing%20vacations%20with%20friends%20instead%20of%20simply%20saying%20that%20the%20trip%20wasn't%20in%20our%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20eliminating%20things%20like%20unnecessary%20cable%20TV%2C%20switched%20to%20a%20cheaper%20cellphone%20carrier%2C%20and%20stopped%20going%20to%20Target%20unnecessarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20paid%20off%20our%20debt%20in%20about%20two%20years%20by%202018%2C%20and%20began%20looking%20for%20what%20we'd%20do%20with%20our%20money%20moving%20forward.%20I%20found%20the%20financial%20independence%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecommunity%20one%20day%20while%20I%20was%20online%20and%20learned%20about%20different%20types%20of%20investing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20realized%20that%20what%20worked%20best%20for%20us%20was%20to%20keep%20investing%20in%20our%20401(k)s%20and%20pensions.%20Every%20time%20we%20got%20a%20raise%2C%20we'd%20ask%20if%20there%20was%20anything%20we%20were%20unsatisfied%20with%20that%20the%20money%20could%20help%20pay%20for.%20The%20answer%20was%20always%20no%2C%20and%20we%20always%20just%20invested%20the%20extra%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f302b2b0-5acc-482a-aada-503c58cd15bd%5C%22%3EI%20was%20delaying%20retirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202021%2C%20we%20felt%20like%20we%20had%20enough%20to%20retire.%20But%20I%20was%20delaying%20quitting%20my%20job%20one%20year%20at%20a%20time%2C%20because%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20imagine%20a%20paycheck%20not%20coming%20in.%20I%20was%20also%20trapped%20in%20golden%20handcuffs%3A%20I%20got%20promoted%20or%20got%20a%20raise%20every%20time%20I%20decided%20to%20walk%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20my%20family%20would%20look%20at%20me%20like%20I%20was%20crazy%20if%20I%20told%20them%20I%20was%20leaving%20%24200%2C000%20a%20year%20behind.%20I%20also%20attached%20my%20work%20to%20my%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20this%20time%2C%20my%20husband%20told%20me%20that%20I%20had%20my%20job%20and%20a%20bunch%20of%20other%20commitments%20in%20front%20of%20me%20and%20that%20he%20felt%20like%20my%20fourth%20priority.%20In%202023%2C%20he%20had%20a%20serious%20heart%20attack.%20When%20I%20was%20waiting%20in%20the%20hospital%2C%20his%20words%20stayed%20with%20me%2C%20and%20I%20realized%20that%20this%20isn't%20what%20I%20want%20him%20to%20believe%20if%20he's%20not%20coming%20back%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22477ae324-0386-4fc0-b356-62014ed598af%5C%22%3EQuitting%20wasn't%20easy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20my%20husband%20had%20died%2C%20I%20would've%20missed%20the%20opportunity%20to%20really%20be%20with%20him%20without%20work%2C%20without%20all%20that%20other%20stuff%20going%20on.%20When%20he%20made%20it%20through%2C%20I%20told%20him%20we're%20retiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20took%20me%20a%20whole%20year%20to%20tell%20my%20company.%20I%20ran%20my%20numbers%20and%20every%20worst-case%20scenario%20with%20a%20friend%2C%20and%20I%20spent%20some%20time%20thinking%20about%20who%20I%20was%20outside%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20settled%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20I%20was%20a%20mom%20and%20wife%20before%20I%20was%20a%20strategist%2C%20things%20fell%20into%20place.%20Since%20March%2C%2