Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%20developed%20a%20wireless%20electronic%20tattoo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c687285e81483682c161d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20device%20measures%20brain%20activity%20and%20eye%20movement%20to%20determine%20mental%20workload.%3Cp%3ENanshu%20Lu%2FUniversity%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20those%20devices%20don't%20analyze%20brain%20activity%20and%20eye%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20years%2C%20we%20developed%20a%20series%20of%20non-invasive%20skin%20conformable%20e-tattoos%20to%20measure%20cardiovascular%20health%2C%20then%20measure%20the%20mental%20stress%20from%20the%20palm%20sweating%2C%26quot%3B%20Lu%20said%20of%20previous%20devices%20she%20helped%20develop.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20finally%2C%20we%20move%20on%20to%20the%20brainwave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELu%20said%20the%20device%20certainly%20isn't%20the%20first%20or%20only%20EEG%20sensor%20on%20the%20market%2C%20but%20it's%20smaller%20and%20lighter%20than%20previous%20models.%20Conducting%20an%20EEG%20test%20typically%20requires%20attaching%20electrodes%20to%20an%20individual's%20full%20scalp%20with%20a%20gel%20or%20paste%20to%20collect%20data%2C%20which%20can%20be%20time-consuming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%20are%20attempting%20to%20streamline%20that%20process%20by%20proving%20mental%20workload%20can%20be%20measured%20only%20from%20the%20forehead.%20During%20lab%20tests%2C%20participants%20did%20memorization%20drills%20that%20involved%20a%20screen%20with%20flashing%20boxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20past%2C%20there%20was%20no%20way%20to%20objectively%20assess%20mental%20workload.%20The%20subjects%20have%20to%20finish%20the%20test%20and%20then%20a%20questionnaire%2C%26quot%3B%20Lu%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20the%20future%2C%20if%20we%20can%20implement%20some%20lightweight%20machine%20learning%20model%20directly%20on%20a%20microprocessor%20in%20the%20Bluetooth%20chip%20on%20e-tattoo%2C%20then%20yes%2C%20our%20goal%20is%20to%20one%20day%20be%20able%20to%20do%20it%20in%20real%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20report%20by%20Grand%20View%20Research%20said%20that%20the%20global%20wearable%20technology%20market%20was%20worth%20%2484.2%20billion%20in%202024%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20%24186.14%20billion%20by%202030%2C%20underscoring%20consumers'%20willingness%20to%20integrate%20technology%20into%20their%20everyday%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20electronic%20tattoos%20won't%20be%20commercial%20anytime%20soon.%20Lu%20and%20her%20fellow%20researchers%20are%20still%20conducting%20tests%20on%20and%20developing%20the%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20can%20imagine%20a%20world%20where%20the%20e-tattoo%20is%20used%20by%20people%20not%20employed%20in%20high-stakes%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20be%20used%20by%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20who%20would%20like%20to%20focus%20as%20well%20as%20people%20who%20want%20to%20meditate%20to%20see%20if%20they%20are%20truly%20relaxed%2C%26quot%3B%20Lu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwearable-tech-face-tattoo-measures-mental-stress-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750021094000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c68a1f748d8c055f3af6f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwearable-tech-face-tattoo-measures-mental-stress-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20device%20developed%20by%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%20looks%20like%20a%20tattoo%20and%20measures%20brain%20activity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40businessinsider.com%20(Lauren%20Edm