20comment%20by%20Business%20Insider%20prior%20to%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20Apple%2C%20I%20think%20it%20was%20Tim%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESteve%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20used%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20Apple%20car%20wash%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThat%20when%20you%20started%20Apple%2C%20they%20kind%20of%20had%20to%20take%20you%20through%20the%20car%20wash%20and%20get%20off%20all%20that%20stuff%20that%20you'd%20accumulated%20at%20other%20places.%20It%20turns%20out%20there's%20a%20car%20wash%20you%20need%20to%20go%20through%20when%20you%20leave%20Apple%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20eschewing%20old%20habits%20as%20you%20move%20into%20a%20new%20role%20is%20important%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20should%20forget%20the%20lessons%20your%20old%20job%20taught%20you%2C%20Baxley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20I%20took%20away%20from%20Apple%2C%20and%20I%20think%20this%20is%20true%20for%20anybody%20changing%20from%20one%20major%20culture%20to%20another%2C%20is%20most%20likely%2C%20the%20new%20place%20hires%20you%20because%20of%20the%20values%20of%20the%20organization%20you%20left%2C%20but%20not%20the%20behaviors%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20move%20on%2C%20it's%20worth%20asking%20how%20you%20can%20best%20incorporate%20the%20best%20aspects%20of%20your%20old%20company's%20culture%20in%20your%20new%20workplace%2C%20Baxley%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20I%20think%20it's%20important%20to%20recalibrate%20and%20say%2C%20well%2C%20I%20want%20to%20hold%20onto%20these%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20at%20Apple%2C%20attention%20to%20detail%2C%20product%20excellence%2C%20doing%20everything%20you%20can%20for%20the%20customer%20and%20the%20user%20%E2%80%94%20so%2C%20try%20to%20hold%20onto%20those%20values%20but%20then%20think%2C%20'Okay%2C%20how%20are%20those%20values%20best%20expressed%20in%20this%20culture%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Baxley%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20it%20won't%20always%20be%20possible%20to%20pause%20between%20roles%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20in%20the%20tech%20sphere%2C%20where%20companies%20usually%20want%20new%20hires%20to%20onboard%20right%20away.%20Even%20if%20you%20have%20to%20start%20immediately%2C%20it%20could%20be%20helpful%20to%20go%20in%20while%20expecting%20a%20period%20of%20adjustment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20biggest%20point%20on%20this%20topic%20is%20that%20when%20you%20go%20into%20a%20new%20culture%20you%20really%20need%20to%20slow%20down%2C%20deeply%20observe%2C%20don't%20judge%20or%20compare%2C%20and%20then%20when%20you%20have%20a%20reasonable%20handle%20on%20things%2C%20reflect%20on%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20express%20the%20values%20from%20the%20old%20place%20with%20behaviors%20that%20are%20appropriate%20to%20the%20new%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-culture-apple-car-wash-new-job-bob-baxley-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749981541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c5db1f748d8c055f3ad53%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-culture-apple-car-wash-new-job-bob-baxley-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bob%20Baxley%20said%20most%20major%20tech%20companies%20have%20very%20%26quot%3Bpowerful%26quot%3B%20cultures%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20can%20sometimes%20accidentally%20follow%20you%20into%20your%20new%20job.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sperkel%40insider.com%20(Sarah%20Perkel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A163%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-culture-apple-car-wash-new-job-bob-baxley-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20dad%20died%20when%20I%20was%207